-- Summary 2: Includes structural invariants, safety assertions, and reachability predicates.
-- Summary 3: Conflicting NFR facts (channel limit <=2 and >=2) cause unsatisfiability.
-- Summary 4: Test case assertions are overly strict and may not hold in all valid scenarios.
-- Assumption 1: Preconditions and postconditions are modeled as abstract states without explicit data.
-- Assumption 2: Actors and permissions are fixed; no dynamic role assignment.
-- Assumption 3: Non-functional requirements are approximated via structural proxies.
